he went into exile in New York, where she acted with Repertorio EspaÃ±ol. Arenas also performed in commercials and did voice over work.  She currently resides in Miami, Florida.</p>\n              </bioghist>\n              <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n              <!-- END CONTROLLED ACCESS TERMS -->\n              <!-- DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- END DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <descgrp>\n                <head>Administrative Information</head>\n                <acqinfo encodinganalog=\"541\">\n                  <head>Acquisition Information:</head>\n                  <p>Gift of Yolanda (Arenas) Sabbatini</p>\n                </acqinfo>\n                <separatedmaterial encodinganalog=\"544 0\">\n                  <head>Separated Materials:</head>\n                  <p>A VHS copy of the film \"Cuba \'58\" was moved to the Videotape Collection.</p>\n                </separatedmaterial>\n                <userestrict encodinganalog=\"540\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Use:</head>\n                  <p>Requests to publish or display materials from this collection require written permission from the rights owner. Please, contact chc@miami.edu for more information.</p>\n                </userestrict>\n                <accessrestrict encodinganalog=\"506\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Access:</head>\n                  <p>Collection is open for research.</p>\n                </accessrestrict>\n                <relatedmaterial encodinganalog=\"544 1\">\n                  <head>Related Materials:</head>\n                  <p>Repertorio EspaÃ±ol Records (CHC5257); INTAR Theatre Records (CHC5159); Herberto DumÃ© Papers (CHC5141); Ofelia GonzÃ¡lez Papers (CHC5241); and Laura Zarrabeitia Papers (CHC5228).  Available in the Cuban Heritage Collection, University of Miami Libraries, Coral Gables, Florida.</p>\n                </relatedmateria