ing aid is written in <language encodinganalog=\"041\" langcode=\"eng\">English</language></langusage>\n              </profiledesc>\n              <revisiondesc>\n                <change encodinganalog=\"583\">\n                  <date type=\"encoded\" normal=\"2013-04-18\">April 18th, 2013</date>\n                  <item>Minimal record added by Amanda Moreno, January 2013.</item>\n                </change>\n              </revisiondesc>\n            </eadheader>\n            <frontmatter>\n              <titlepage>\n                <titleproper encodinganalog=\"245\">Guide to the ASCE (Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy) Collection\n                        </titleproper>\n                <publisher encodinganalog=\"260$b\">University of Miami Cuban Heritage Collection</publisher>\n              </titlepage>\n            </frontmatter>\n            <archdesc level=\"collection\" type=\"inventory\" audience=\"external\" relatedencoding=\"MARC21\">\n              <did>\n                <head>Overview of the Collection</head>\n                <unittitle label=\"Collection Title\" encodinganalog=\"245\">ASCE (Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy) Collection                              <unitdate label=\"Dates\" encodinganalog=\"245$f\" type=\"inclusive\">1996</unitdate></unittitle>\n                <unitid encodinganalog=\"035\" label=\"Identification\" repositorycode=\"US-FQG\" countrycode=\"US\">01/CHC0514</unitid>\n                <origination label=\"Creator\" encodinganalog=\"245$c\">\n                  <corpname encodinganalog=\"110\" normal=\"Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy (ASCE)\" source=\"lcnaf\" role=\"Collector\">Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy (ASCE)</corpname>\n                </origination>\n                <physdesc label=\"Physical Description\">\n                  <extent encodinganalog=\"300\" type=\"Linear Feet\">0.50</extent>\n                </physdesc>\n                <repository encodinganalog=\"852$b\" label=\"Repository\">\n                  <corpname>University of Miami Cuban Heritage Collection</corpname>\n                  <address>\n                    <addressline>University of Miami Libraries</addressline>\n                    <addressline>1300 Memorial Drive</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Coral Gables, FL, </addressline>\n                    <addressline>URL: http://library.miami.edu/chc/</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Email: chc@miami.edu</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Phone: (305) 284-4900</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Fax: (305) 284-4901</addressline>\n                  </address>\n                </repository>\n                <abstract encodinganalog=\"520$a\" label=\"Abstract\">The ASCE (Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy) Collection consists of conference papers on various topics relating to the Cuban economic transition, the contents of which were published in book form.</abstract>\n              </did>\n              <!--COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA: -->\n              <bioghist altrender=\"Historical Note\" encodinganalog=\"545\">\n                <head>Historical Note:</head>\n                <p>The Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy (ASCE) is a non-partisan, non-profit organization whose primary mission is to \"study the elements and processes involved in a transition to a free market economy and a democracy [in Cuba], as well as to promote scholarship, research, and publications on transition studies by its members.\"</p>\n                <p>ASCE is affiliated with the American Economic Association and the Allied Social Sciences Association of the United States. The group works with economists on the island who wish to engage in scholarly discussion and research.</p>\n              </bioghist>\n              <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n              <!-- END CONTROLLED ACCESS TERMS -->\n              <!-- DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- END DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <descgrp>\n                <head>Administrative Information</head>\n                <processinfo encodinganalog=\"583\">\n                  <head>Processing Information:</head>\n                  <p>This collection is currently in processing.</p>\n                </processinfo>\n                <userestrict encodinganalog=\"540\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Use:</head>\n                  <p>Requests to publish or display materials from this collection require written permission from the rights owner. Please contact <extref linktype=\"simple\" audience=\"external\" show=\"embed\" actuate=\"onrequest\" href=\"mailto:chc@miami.edu\">chc@miami.edu</extref> for more information.</p>\n                </userestrict>\n                <accessrestrict encodinganalog=\"506\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Access:</head>\n                  <p>This collection is open for research.</p>\n                </accessrestrict>\n                <prefercite encodinganalog=\"524\">\n                  <head>Preferred Citation:</head>\n                  <p>ASCE (Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy) Collection, Cuban Heritage Collection, University of Miami Libraries, Coral Gables, Florida</p>\n                </prefercite>\n              </descgrp>\n              <scopecontent>\n                <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                <p>The ASCE (Association for the Study of the Cuban Economy) Collection consists of twenty-two papers presented by panelists at the VI Annual Meeting of ASCE, held at the University of Miami from August 8th-10th, 1996.</p>\n                <p>These papers, as well as proceedings from the conference, have been published in a series of <emph render=\"italic\">Cuba in Transition</emph>. Paper topics cover a wide range of subjects, from overviews of the general economic problems of  a transition to a market economy in Cuba to studies of specific economic sectors such as tourism, trade policy, banking, energy, agriculture and the sugar industry.</p>\n              </scopecontent>\n              <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n              <!-- END SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n            </archdesc>\n          </ead>\n        </objectXMLWrap>\n      </resourceRelation>\n    </relations>\n  </cpfDescription>\n</eac-cpf>\n',0,'/Applications/MAMP/htdocs/eac/ead/asce_association_for_the_study_of_the_cuban_economy_collection.xml','2013-06-27 15:27:26','2013-06-27 11:27:26'),(20,'<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<eac-cpf xmlns=\"urn:isbn:1-931666-33-4\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" xmlns:ead=\"urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9\" xmlns:owl=\"http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#\" xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\" xmlns:eac=\"http://eac.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/schema/cpf.xsd\" xmlns:php=\"http://php.net/xsl\">\n  <control>\n    <recordId>asociacin_cubana_de_mujeres_universitarias_acmu</recordId>\n    <maintenanceStatus>new</maintenanceStatus>\n    <publicationStatus>inProcess</publicationStatus>\n    <maintenanceAgency>\n      <agencyCode>FMU-N</agencyCode>\n      <otherAgencyCode localType=\"oclc\">FQG</otherAgencyCode>\n      <agencyName>University of Miami Libraries</agencyName>\n    </maintenanceAgency>\n    <languageDeclaration>\n      <language languageCode=\"eng\">English</language>\n      <script scriptCode=\"Latn\">Latin</script>\n    </languageDeclaration>\n    <maintenanceHistory>\n      <maintenanceEvent>\n        <eventType>created</eventType>\n        <eventDateTime standardDateTime=\"2013-06-27\"/>\n        <agentType>machine</agentType>\n        <agent>ead2eac.xsl</agent>\n      </maintenanceEvent>\n    </maintenanceHistory>\n    <sources>\n      <source xlink:type=\"simple\" xlink:href=\"http://proust.library.miami.edu/findingaids/?p=collection