1300 Memorial Drive</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Coral Gables, FL, </addressline>\n                    <addressline>URL: http://library.miami.edu/chc/</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Email: chc@miami.edu</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Phone: (305) 284-4900</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Fax: (305) 284-4901</addressline>\n                  </address>\n                </repository>\n                <note encodinganalog=\"500\" label=\"Note\">\n                  <p>Other Information:</p>\n                  <p>Additional information may be found at http://proust.library.miami.edu/findingaids/legacy/chc0273CL.pdf</p>\n                </note>\n              </did>\n              <!--COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA: -->\n              <bioghist altrender=\"Biographical Information\" encodinganalog=\"545\">\n                <head>Biographical Information:</head>\n                <p>Eduardo Ãviles RamÃ­rez was born in Juigalpa, Nicaragua, and enjoyed a distinguished career as a journalist, poet, and scholar for more than sixty years. Ãviles RamÃ­rez arrived in Cuba as a young man and wrote articles for many newspapers and magazines. He acquired a wide following among Cubans, who came to regard him as a native of Havana. Ãviles RamÃ­rez ultimately joined the renowned circles of Cuban journalists and intellectuals. Through his endeavors in the field of poetry, Ãviles RamÃ­rez is included in the anthology of Cuban poetry.</p>\n                <p>In 1922, Ãviles RamÃ­rez undertook his final trip to Nicaragua, where he met Ruben DarÃ­o, a prominent literary figure. In 1925, Ãviles RamÃ­rez arrived in Paris for the first time. He remained there until the outbreak of World War II. Much of his literary work pertains to Paris and its residents. In 1940, Ãviles RamÃ­rez was detained and situated outside of the city. Hispanic American diplomats formed a literary discourse, and Ãviles RamÃ­rez seized this opportunity to pay tribute to Ruben DarÃ­o.</p>\n                <p>Eduardo Ãviles RamÃ­rez traveled around the world, and reported personal experiences on journeys to places such as Constantinople. Ãviles RamÃ­rez also wrote about prominent individuals and literary writers. He published a few books and also formed a collection of letters and photographs he had received from different parts of the world. He wrote for newspapers such as Diario de YucatÃ¡n, El Universal, El PaÃ­s, and Diario de la Marina. He wrote for magazines such as Bohemia, GrÃ¡fos, Puerto Rico Ilustrado, and Revista Cubana.</p>\n                <p>Eduardo Ãviles RamÃ­rez became ill, but his conviction to write did not subside. Despite his infirmity and physical disability to correspond, he would dictate articles to his daughter Yolanda, and she would have them published. Mr. Ãviles RamÃ­rezâ€™s last article was published in 1989. He died on June 28, 1989 in Paris.</p>\n              </bioghist>\n              <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n              <!-- END CONTROLLED ACCESS TERMS -->\n              <!-- DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- END DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <descgrp>\n                <head>Administrative Information</head>\n                <acqinfo encodinganalog=\"541\">\n                  <head>Acquisition Information:</head>\n                  <p>Gift of Yolanda Aviles, 1990.Â  Correspondence transferred from the GastÃ³n Baquero Papers, October 2006.</p>\n                </acqinfo>\n                <userestrict encodinganalog=\"540\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Use:</head>\n                  <p>Requests to publish or display materials from this collection require written permission from the rights owner. Please, contact chc@miami.edu for more information.</p>\n                </userestrict>\n                <accessrestrict encodinganalog=\"506\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Access:</head>\n                  <p>This collection is open for research.</p>\n                </accessrestrict>\n                <prefercite encodinganalog=\"524\">\n                  <head>Preferred Citation:</head>\n                  <p>Eduardo AvilÃ©s RamÃ­rez Collection, Cuban Heritage Collection, University of Miami Libraries, Coral Gables, Florida</p>\n                </prefercite>\n              </descgrp>\n              <arrangement encodinganalog=\"351\">\n                <head>Arrangement of Materials:</head>\n                <p>The Eduardo Ãviles RamÃ­rez Collection is organized into six series.</p>\n                <p>Please see the Finding Aid/Inventory section of this guide for more detailed information.</p>\n              </arrangement>\n              <scopecontent>\n                <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                <p>The Eduardo Ãviles RamÃ­rez Collection consists of newspaper and magazine articles which pertain to his personal experiences with various cultures and with the lifestyles of many prominent individuals, such as Francis de Miomandre and Ruben DarÃ­o.</p>\n                <p>Articles date from the early 1920s to the late 1980s. The bulk of the collection consists of periodicals and clippings written for Latin American publications in Cuba, Mexico, Nicaragua, and Venezuela.</p>\n                <p>The collection also contains numerous articles written about Ruben DarÃ­o, a notable Nicaraguan literary figure, for newspapers such as InformaciÃ³n, Diario de la Marina, and El Universal. Many articles relating to Spain also appear in Latin American publications such as Puerto Rico Ilustrado and Diario de YucatÃ¡n. The collection also includes a substantial number of articles illustrated by Ricardo Marin, a famous Cuban illustrator. Marin illustrated articles for publications such as InformaciÃ³n and Diario de la Marina from 1938 to 1940.</p>\n              </scopecontent>\n              <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n              <!-- BEGIN SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n              <dsc type=\"combined\">\n                <head>Detailed List of Contents</head>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6300</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Cuba Clippings</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1926-1960</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series consists of two boxes of newspaper and magazine articles from Cuban publications, 1926-1960. Box 1 contains clippings from Arte y DecoraciÃ³n, Bohemia, and Diario de la Marina. Box 2 contains clippings from Habano, InformaciÃ³n, El PaÃ­s, Pro-Arte Musical, and Revista Cubana.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                  <c02 level=\"file\">\n                    <did>\n                      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id46942</unitid>\n                      <container type=\"Box\">1</container>\n                    </did>\n                    <c03 level=\"file\">\n                      <did>\n                        <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id46943</unitid>\n                        <container type=\"Box\">1</container>\n                        <container type=\"Folder\">55</container>\n                        <unittitle>Correspondence from unid. To Porfirio Valiente</unittitle>\n                        <unitdate>unid.</unitdate>\n                      </did>\n                      <descgrp>\n                        <accessrestrict>\n                          <head>Access Restriction</head>\n                          <p>n.d., 1855, 1869</p>\n                        </accessrestrict>\n                      </descgrp>\n                      <scopecontent>\n                        <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                        <p>Valiente, Porfirio</p>\n                      </scopecontent>\n                    </c03>\n                  </c02>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6301</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Mexico Clippings</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1928-1980</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series consists of three boxes of newspaper and magazine articles from Mexican publications, 1928-1980. Boxes 3-5 contain clippings from Diario de YucatÃ¡n, Excelsior, El Informador, El Nacional, El Porvenir, Revista Norte, El Sol de MÃ©xico, and Universal.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6302</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Nicaragua Clippings</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1926-1963</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series consists of one box of newspaper and magazine articles from Nicaraguan publications, 1926-1963. Box 5 contains clippings from El Grafico, La Noticia Ilustrada, Pantalla, La Prensa, and RenovaciÃ³n.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6303</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Venezuela Clippings</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>1953-1981</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series consists of two boxes of newspaper and magazine articles from Venezuelan publications, 1953-1981. Boxes 5-6 contain clippings from El Nacional and El Universal.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6304</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Periodicals and Clippings (oversize)</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1926-1985</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series consists of one box of oversized newspaper and magazine articles from various publications, 1926-1985. Box 7 includes clippings from El Heraldo, Bohemia, Diario de la Marina, El PaÃ­s, Grafos, InformaciÃ³n, La Prensa, El Informador, El Nacional, El Sol de MÃ©xico, Puerto Rico Ilustrado, and La Voz Libre.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6305</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Special Topic Clippings</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series consists of one box of newspaper and magazine articles from various publications. Box 8 includes articles about Ruben DarÃ­o, articles illustrated by Ricardo Marin, articles about Spain, and miscellaneous articles.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id66607</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Photographs</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>circa 1900-1980</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <c02 level=\"file\">\n                    <did>\n                      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id66609</unitid>\n                      <container type=\"Box\">11</container>\n                    </did>\n                    <c03 level=\"file\">\n                      <did>\n                        <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id66610</unitid>\n                        <container type=\"Box\">11</container>\n                        <container type=\"Folder\">83</container>\n                        <unittitle>Photographs</unittitle>\n                        <unitdate>circa 1900-1980</unitdate>\n                      </did>\n                      <scopecontent>\n                        <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                        <p>Twelve photographs of various Cuban artists, musicians, and writers. Many are signed by the subject and addressed to Eduardo AvilÃ©s RamÃ­rez.</p>\n                      </scopecontent>\n                    </c03>\n                  </c02>\n                </c01>\n              </dsc>\n              <!-- END SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n            </archdesc>\n          </ead>\n        </objectXMLWrap>\n      </resourceRelation>\n    </relations>\n  </cpfDescription>\n</eac-cpf>\n',0,'/Applications/MAMP/htdocs/eac/ead/avils_ramrez_eduardo_collection_19261985.xml','2013-06-27 15:27:26','2013-06-27 11:27:26'),(28,'<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<eac-cpf xmlns=\"urn:isbn:1-931666-33-4\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" xmlns:ead=\"urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9\" xmlns:owl=\"http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#\" xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\" xmlns:eac=\"http://eac.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/schema/cpf.xsd\" xmlns:php=\"http://php.net/xsl\">\n  <control>\n    <recordId>bacard_amalia_collection</recordId>\n    <maintenanceStatus>new</maintenanceStatus>\n    <publicationStatus>inProcess</publicati