ks, Memorial de un testigo, in 1966. In 1984 a collection of his works was compiled and published under the title Magias e invenciones.</p>\n                <p>In 1988 Baquero was nominated for the prestigious â€œPremio PrÃ­ncipe de Asturias de las Letras.â€ A collection of his essays in two volumes, Indios, blancos y negros en el caldero de America, was published in 1991 and AutoantologÃ­a comentada in 1992. He became a finalist to the 1992 â€œPremio Nacional de Literaturaâ€ in poetry for Poemas Invisibles, and was nominated for other important awards such as the â€œReina SofÃ­a.â€ In 1993 the â€œFray Luis de LeÃ³nâ€ Poetry Chair of the University of Salamanca celebrated a week-long conference in honor of his poetic works. Other tributes included the inclusion of two volumes of his work in the â€œObras Maestrasâ€ collection of â€œFundaciÃ³n Central Hispano.â€</p>\n                <p>Not until 1994, however, was his work recognized in his native Cuba, when a conference about his poetry was held at the University of Havana for the first time since he left the country. Baquero died in Madrid on May 15, 1997.</p>\n              </bioghist>\n              <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n              <!-- END CONTROLLED ACCESS TERMS -->\n              <!-- DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- END DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <descgrp>\n                <head>Administrative Information</head>\n                <acqinfo encodinganalog=\"541\">\n                  <head>Acquisition Information:</head>\n                  <p>Purchased from GastÃ³n Baquero with funds donated by the AMIGOS of the Cuban Heritage Collection and other donors, 1996</p>\n                </acqinfo>\n                <processinfo encodinganalog=\"583\">\n                  <head>Processing Information:</head>\n                  <p>Encoded by: Isabel Ezquerra, Esperanza de Varona and Marta MartÃ­nez 25 October, 2006</p>\n                  <p>Retrospectively converted from HTML to EAD XML September, 2008 by Lyn MacCorkle and Kyle Rimkus based on a crosswalk by MarÃ­a Estorino.</p>\n                </processinfo>\n                <separatedmaterial encodinganalog=\"544 0\">\n                  <head>Separated Materials:</head>\n                  <p>The correspondence of author and journalist Eduardo AvilÃ©s RamÃ­rez, sent to GastÃ³n Baquero by AvilÃ©s RamÃ­rezâ€™s daughter Yolanda and originally part of this collection, has been added to the AvilÃ©s RamÃ­rez Collection, CHC0273.</p>\n                </separatedmaterial>\n                <userestrict encodinganalog=\"540\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Use:</head>\n                  <p>Requests to publish or display materials from this collection require written permission from the rights owner. Please, contact chc@miami.edu for more information.</p>\n                </userestrict>\n                <accessrestrict encodinganalog=\"506\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Access:</head>\n                  <p>This collection is unrestricted.</p>\n                </accessrestrict>\n                <prefercite encodinganalog=\"524\">\n                  <head>Preferred Citation:</head>\n                  <p>The GastÃ³n Baquero Papers, Cuban Heritage Collection, University of Miami Libraries.</p>\n                </prefercite>\n              </descgrp>\n              <arrangement encodinganalog=\"351\">\n                <head>Arrangement of Materials:</head>\n                <p>The GastÃ³n Baquero Papers are organized into eight series.</p>\n                <p>Please the Finding Aid/Inventory section of this guide for more detailed information.</p>\n              </arrangement>\n              <scopecontent>\n                <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                <p>The collection consists of documents, books and other materials written and collected by Cuban writer GastÃ³n Baquero during the last years of his life in Madrid, Spain. The collection includes correspondence, published and unpublished works by Baquero, clippings of newspaper articles by and about Baquero, research notes, photographs, clippings, scrapbooks, awards and memorabilia. Although the collection includes personal papers and documents, the bulk of materials relates to the subjects that occupied Baquero throughout his life, namely Cuban, Spanish and Latin American literature, history and politics.</p>\n              </scopecontent>\n              <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n              <!-- BEGIN SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n              <dsc type=\"combined\">\n                <head>Detailed List of Contents</head>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6279</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Works: Manuscripts and Notes</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1935-1994</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Manuscripts and typescripts of published and unpublished books and articles by GastÃ³n Baquero accompanied by related materials such as correspondence related to their publication. Among these is Baqueroâ€™s unpublished book about AndrÃ©s Bello and related research materials. Also included are articles about Baquero. Subseries C, Conferences and Conference Notes, contains printed materials related to Baqueroâ€™s lectures.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                  <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n                    <did>\n                      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6280</unitid>\n                      <unittitle>Books</unittitle>\n                      <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>\n                    </did>\n                    <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n      