       <titlepage>\n                <titleproper encodinganalog=\"245\">Guide to the Laureano Batista Falla Papers\n                              <date normal=\"1961/1992\" encodinganalog=\"260$c\">1961/1992</date></titleproper>\n                <publisher encodinganalog=\"260$b\">University of Miami Cuban Heritage Collection</publisher>\n              </titlepage>\n            </frontmatter>\n            <archdesc level=\"collection\" type=\"inventory\" audience=\"external\" relatedencoding=\"MARC21\">\n              <did>\n                <head>Overview of the Collection</head>\n                <unittitle label=\"Collection Title\" encodinganalog=\"245\">Laureano Batista Falla Papers                              <unitdate label=\"Dates\" encodinganalog=\"245$f\" type=\"inclusive\" normal=\"1961/1992\">1961-1992</unitdate></unittitle>\n                <unitid encodinganalog=\"035\" label=\"Identification\" repositorycode=\"US-FQG\" countrycode=\"US\">01/CHC0333</unitid>\n                <origination label=\"Creator\" encodinganalog=\"245$c\">\n                  <persname encodinganalog=\"100\" normal=\"Batista Falla, Laureano\" source=\"local\" role=\"Collector\">Batista Falla, Laureano</persname>\n                </origination>\n                <physdesc label=\"Physical Description\">\n                  <extent encodinganalog=\"300\" type=\"Boxes\">35.00</extent>\n                </physdesc>\n                <langmaterial encodinganalog=\"546\" label=\"Language of Materials\">\n                  <language encodinganalog=\"041\" langcode=\"spa\">Spanish;Castilian</language>\n                </langmaterial>\n                <repository encodinganalog=\"852$b\" label=\"Repository\">\n                  <corpname>University of Miami Cuban Heritage Collection</corpname>\n                  <address>\n                    <addressline>University of Miami Libraries</addressline>\n                    <addressline>1300 Memorial Drive</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Coral Gables, FL, </addressline>\n                    <addressline>URL: http://library.miami.edu/chc/</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Email: chc@miami.edu</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Phone: (305) 284-4900</addressline>\n                    <addressline>Fax: (305) 284-4901</addressline>\n                  </address>\n                </repository>\n                <note encodinganalog=\"500\" label=\"Note\">\n                  <p>Other Information:</p>\n                  <p>Additional information may be found at http://proust.library.miami.edu/findingaids/legacy/chc0333.pdf</p>\n                </note>\n              </did>\n              <!--COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA: -->\n              <bioghist altrender=\"Biographical Information\" encodinganalog=\"545\">\n                <head>Biographical Information:</head>\n                <p>Laureano F. Batista Falla was born in Havana, Cuba, on May 1, 1935.  He received his elementary and secodary education in De la Salle School, Vedado, Havana, Cuba.  In 1952, he entered the Law School of the Universidad Santo TomÃ¡s de Villanueva, Marianao, Cuba, and in 1953, he was admitted at the Ã‹scuela de FilosofÃ­a y Letras\" of the University of Havana as a part time student.  After his graduation in 1957 from Universidad Santo TomÃ¡s de Villanueva as a Doctor of Law, he spent a year in Germany to study the German language and did special studies in banking at the Deutsch Bank A. G. Hamburg and Munich.  In January 1959, he returned to Havana, Cuba and was employed in the Legal Department of the Trust company of Cuba.  In 1960, he was compelled to leave Cuba by force of circumstances and came to Miami as an exile.</p>\n                <p>Batista Falla fought for Cuba\'s freedom in Cuba and from the exile.  In 1960, he founded with JosÃ© Ignacio Rasco and others the Movimiento DemÃ³crata Cristiano de Cuba and was also the president of the Catholic Student Youth (J.E.C.).  Laureano worked actively against Castro\'s Communist regime within the \"Movimiento DemÃ³crata Cristiano de Cuba en el Exilio\" (M.D.C.) and organized clandestine operations against the Cuban government.  He was a member of the delegations representing the M.D.C. at different congresses such as Ã–rganizaciÃ³n DemÃ³crata Cristiana de AmÃ©rica\" of which the M.D.C. was a member in Lima, PerÃº, Santiago de Chile, Strasbourg, Caracas, etc.</p>\n                <p>Laureano received a Masters Degree in Government from University of Miami and later a Ph.D. in Political Science from Georgetown University, Waschington, D.C., in the late 1960s.</p>\n                <p>He lived in Venezuela for several years, where he was a professor at the Universidad CatÃ³lica AndrÃ©s Bello, and occupied important positions in different organizations, such as Centro de InformaciÃ³n y DocumentaciÃ³n para AmÃ©rica Latina (C.I.D.A.L.), Ecodata, C.A., and Cibernetica Internacional, C.A.</p>\n                <p>When Batista returned to Miami, he founded the Cuban exile publication Revista RaÃ­z, together with Alberto PÃ©rez, Marta FernÃ¡ndez Morell, Raquel la Villa and others.  He was also the director of the Instituto Jacques Maritain in Miami.</p>\n                <p>Laureano Batista was a tireless advocate of pluralism and democracy and in the last years of his life he organized the \"Partido DemÃ³crata Cristiano de Cuba,\" a political party composed of former members of different organizations who fought for the Cuban freedom.  He died in Miami in 1991.</p>\n              </bioghist>\n              <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n              <!-- END CONTROLLED ACCESS TERMS -->\n              <!-- DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- END DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n              <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <descgrp>\n                <head>Administrative Information</head>\n                <acqinfo encodinganalog=\"541\">\n                  <head>Acquisition Information:</head>\n                  <p>Gift of Adela Batista, 1992.</p>\n                </acqinfo>\n                <userestrict encodinganalog=\"540\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Use:</head>\n                  <p>Requests to publish or display materials from this collection require written permission from the rights owner. Please, contact chc@miami.edu for more information.</p>\n                </userestrict>\n                <accessrestrict encodinganalog=\"506\">\n                  <head>Conditions Governing Access:</head>\n                  <p>This collection is open for research.</p>\n                </accessrestrict>\n                <prefercite encodinganalog=\"524\">\n                  <head>Preferred Citation:</head>\n                  <p>Laureano Batista Falla Papers, Cuban Heritage Collection, University of Miami Libraries, Coral Gables, Florida</p>\n                </prefercite>\n              </descgrp>\n              <arrangement encodinganalog=\"351\">\n                <head>Arrangement of Materials:</head>\n                <p>The Laureano Batista Falla Papers are organized into eight series.</p>\n                <p>Please see the Finding Aid/Iventory section of this guide for more detailed information.</p>\n              </arrangement>\n              <scopecontent>\n                <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                <p>The Laureano Batista Falla Papers consists of personal files, human rights material, records of the \"Luna\"Mission, the Movimiento DemÃ³crata Cristiano, the OrganizaciÃ³n DemÃ³crata Cristiana de AmÃ©rica, political parties, and general material of other associations/institutions and publications.Â  This collection consists of 816 folders in 35 boxes, arranged in eight series.</p>\n              </scopecontent>\n              <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n              <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n              <!-- BEGIN SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n              <dsc type=\"combined\">\n                <head>Detailed List of Contents</head>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6308</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Personal Files</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1960-1990</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (boxes 1-5) consists of articles, correspondence, manuscripts, theses, conferences, photographs, speeches, curricula vitae, sketches and personal documents.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6309</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Movimiento DemÃ³crata Cristiano (M.D.C.)</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1959-1990</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (boxes 6-20) includes by-laws and objectives, clippings, conferences, congresses, correspondence, delegations, events, financial records, publications, pamphlets, periodicals and seminars among other general records.  This series also contains records of the ComitÃ© Ejecutivo and the Departamento Militar of the M.D.C. as well as records of institutions affiliated to the M.D.C.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6310</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Luna\" Mission</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1964-1967</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (boxes 21-22) contains correspondence, collaborators, financial records, publications, travels and general material pertaining to the mission which is divided in three parts Luna I, II and III.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6311</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>OrganizaciÃ³n DemÃ³crata Cristiana de AmÃ©rica (ODCA)</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (boxes 23-26) consists of by-laws, clippings, congresses, correspondence, declarations, publications, general information on affiliated political parties, organizations in Latin America and Europe, and other general material.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6312</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Political Parties</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (boxes 27-28) includes by-laws, clippings, congresses and conferences, elections, publications, correspondence among other material pertaining to political parties in Latin AmÃ©rica and Europe.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6313</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Human Rights</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1984</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (box 29) contains correspondence, speeches, material about political prisoners and several records of the United Nations and Centro de Derechos Humanos (CEDEHU) among other material.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6314</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Associations and Institutions</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1961-1990</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (boxes 30-34) consists of by-laws, clippings, correspondence, congresses, press releases, seminars, publications, surveys and other material pertaining to various associations and institutions.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"series\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6315</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Miscellaneous</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>n.d., 1935-1991</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The series (box 35) contains clippings, news releases, periodicals, reports as well as some material related to John F. Kennedy\'s assassination.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n              </dsc>\n              <!-- END SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n            </archdesc>\n          </ead>\n        </objectXMLWrap>\n      </resourceRelation>\n    </relations>\n  </cpfDescription>\n</eac-cpf>\n',0,'/Applications/MAMP/htdocs/eac/ead/batista_falla_laureano_papers.xml','2013-06-27 15:27:27','2013-06-27 11:27:27'),(40,'<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<