 2011.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79682</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>DÃ­az Espinosa, Maribel</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 June 26</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Daughter of renowned Cuban pianist and music instructor Conchita Espinosa. Conchita founded music academies in Cuba and the United States, receiving numerous awards as a distinguished educator. Maribel currently runs her late mother\'s school, Conchita Espinosa Academy.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79683</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>DÃºran, Alfredo</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 November 5</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Bay of Pigs veteran who chaired the Florida Democratic Party from 1976 to 1980.Â  Appointed by Florida governor Reubin Askew in 1973, he was the first Hispanic to serve on the Miami-Dade County School Board. A former president of the Veteranâ€™s Association of Brigade 2506, DurÃ¡n was asked to step down for his support of a dialogue with the Cuban government to bring about a transition in Cuba.Â  He founded the Cuban Committee for Democracy in 1993.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79684</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Fajardo, Josefina</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 October 20</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>First wife of Cuban flutist and internationally renowned bandleader JosÃ© Fajardo.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79685</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Feldenkreis, George</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 February 8</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>CEO and Chairman of Perry Ellis International and prominent member of the Cuban Jewish community.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79686</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>FernÃ¡ndez, Camilo</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 January 15</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>One of the founders of the AsociaciÃ³n Pro Cuba (Pro-Cuba Association) of Elizabeth, New Jersey and president of the Junta PatriÃ³tica Cubana (Patriotic Cuban Junta) in that area.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79687</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Ferreira M.D., Leonor</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 September 26</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Civic leader and one of the first Cuban female physicians actively involved in the University of Havana and political struggles of her times. Ferreira is a founding and active member of the Miami-based organization Junta PatriÃ³tica Cubana.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79688</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Fiallo Pascual, Delia</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 September 29</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Author of radio dramas and television novellas, who found success both in pre-Revolutionary Cuba and after her exile in the United States. Among her most famous works are Soraya, El Angel Perverso, and Lidia Sandoval.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79689</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Fleitas, AndrÃ©s</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 June 29</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Legend of Cuban baseball and distinguished player in the old Cuban professional league and internationally who was elected to the Cuban Baseball Hall of Fame in 1971.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79690</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>GarcÃ­a, Jaime</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 November 21</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Pianist, chief arranger, and founder of Miami\'s Conjunto Universal.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79691</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>GarcÃ­a FustÃ©, TomÃ¡s</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 December 8</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Pioneer of Cuban radio in Miami.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79692</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Germain, Miguel</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 July 11</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban activist of Haitian descent who served as president of Municipios de Cuba en el Exilio in the early 1970s, which probably made him the first black Cuban to preside over a Cuban exile organization in Miami.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79693</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Goderich, Mario P.</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 May 22</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban-born lawyer who became the first Cuban-American appointed and later elected as a judge in the Third and Eleventh Judicial Circuit Courts of Florida.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79694</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>GÃ³mez GÃ³mez, JosÃ©</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 June 7</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>One of the thousands of Spaniards who emigrated from Galicia to Cuba and established himself in the Cuban middle class of the 1950s. GÃ³mez GÃ³mez followed his Cuban family and friends into exile in Miami, where he was one of the founders and still is the driving force of the Casa de Santa Marta de Ortigueira.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79695</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>GonzÃ¡lez, Fidel</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 March 7</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>A defense attorney for many death penalty candidates before Cuba\'s revolutionary courts, who soon became a target himself of the dictatorship. Dr. GonzÃ¡lez was one of the early Cuban exiles in the New York-New Jersey region, where he has been actively involved in the patriotic and civic endeavors of the area\'s Cuban community.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79696</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Grau de Santeiro, MarÃ­a</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 February 20</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Granddaughter of Gerardo Machado y Morales, fifth president of Cuba.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79697</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>GutiÃ©rrez, Carlos</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 August 14</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban-American businessman and political figure. GutiÃ©rrez served as CEO of Kelloggâ€™s corporation from 1999-2004, and is attributed as saving the company from bankruptcy. He left his post to join George W. Bushâ€™s administration in 2004, as the 35th US Secretary of Commerce.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79698</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>HernÃ¡ndez, Francisco \"Pepe\" J.</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 October 15</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>President of the Cuban American National Foundation.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79699</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Huertas M.D., Enrique</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 January 6</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>President of Colegio MÃ©dico Cubano Libre (Free Cuban Medical College) and a leader in the Cuban exile community.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79700</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Iriondo, Sylvia G.</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 February 29</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Founder and President of Mothers Against Repression (MAR), an organization that fights for the democratization of Cuba. Iriondo is an internationally recognized human rights activist.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79701</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Jorge, Antonio</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 October 28</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Professor of economics at Florida International University, who has worked extensively on the economic reconstruction of Cuba.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79702</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Le Matt, JosÃ©</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 June 22</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Operatic and lyric singer and musical director who performed with the Orquesta FilarmÃ³nica de La Habana, and directed the Teatro de la Opera de La Habana in Cuba. He has performed in Spain, Italy, New York and Miami, sharing the stage with legendary performers such as Renata Tebaldi and Monserrat CaballÃ©.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79703</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>LeÃ³n Jr., BenjamÃ­n</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2009 October 28</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Founder and CEO of Leon Medical Centers (LMC), a seven-clinic medical group that focuses on healthcare for Hispanic seniors.Â  With his father, LeÃ³n ran Miamiâ€™s first pre-paid medical center, Clinica AsociaciÃ³n Cubana.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79704</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Levitan, Aida</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 August 22</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban-American businesswoman who served as CEO and vice-Chairperson of Bromley Communications, a national advertising and public relations firm. She currently heads her own marketing company, The Levitan Group, Inc.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79705</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Lezama Lima, Eloisa</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2009 May 22</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Sister and confidant of Cubaâ€™s great poet JosÃ© Lezama Lima.Â </p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79706</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>LÃ³pez Jr., Camilo</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 May 16</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Son of the founder of Cuba\'s Camilo Muebles (Camilo Furniture) who re-launched the family business in exile in Miami.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79707</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Lopez, Tony</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2009 June 13</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban sculptor.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79708</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Luna, Laura</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 September 16</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban post-modernist visual artist who is part of the \"80s Golden Generation.\" Luna and her family obtained political asylum in the US during the Mariel Boatlift of 1980, after which she established a studio in Miami in 1994.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79709</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Machado, Gus</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 February 3</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Founder of one of largest Hispanic car dealerships in the United States and philanthropist.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79710</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>MartÃ­nez, Eugenio Rolando \"Musculito\"</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 June 29</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Considered to be the Cuban who infiltrated the island more times that anyone else as a CIA agent and member of the Movimiento de RecuperaciÃ³n Revolucionaria (MRR). He also was one of the four \"plumbers\" in the Watergate scandal.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79711</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Mas Santos, Jorge</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 August 4</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>American-born son of exile leader Jorge Mas Canosa, CEO of MasTec, and president of the Cuban American National Foundation.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79712</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Matos Sr., Huber</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2008 April 23; 2008 May 1; 2008 May 7</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Famous â€œcomandanteâ€ of Castroâ€™s guerrilla, first Commander-in-Chief of CamagÃ¼ey province. Jailed for 20 years for denouncing Castroâ€™s communist leanings in October 1959. Director of the anti-Castro exile group â€œCuba Independiente y DemocrÃ¡tica.â€</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79713</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Medrano, Humberto</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 September 13</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Journalist and former sub-director of Cubaâ€™s Prensa Libre. Director of Radio and TV MartÃ­ in exile.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79714</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>MenÃ©ndez, Demetrio</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 July 5</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Set designer, stage manager, entertainment entrepreneur, musician, and all-around behind-the-scenes man of Cuban performing arts who helped found AÃ±orada Cuba and Sociedad Pro-Arte Grateli. MenÃ©ndez was a TV set designer at CMQ TV in Cuba. As an exile, he traveled the world with the Margot Fontayne Ballet Co. before settling in Miami where he is still active in the entertainment industry.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79715</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Mesa-MartÃ­ Betancourt Sharpe, Lidia</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 January 16</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Widow of Juan RenÃ© Betancourt, president of the Federation of Cuban Societies of Color who wrote a number of books about racial discrimination in Cuba in the 1950s.Â  Mrs. Sharpe is owner of the Little Havana Restaurant on Cornelia Street in Manhattan.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79716</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>O\'Farrill, Albertina</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>29 March 2008; 2008 April 4</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Former political prisoner who served time with Polita Grau.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79717</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>PaÃ­s, AgustÃ­n</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 October 17</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Brother of Frank PaÃ­s, who is regarded by many as the one revolutionary leader who could rival Fidel Castro in the struggle against Batista. Frank was killed in a Santiago de Cuba uprising that was planned to unfold at the time that Castro was reaching Cuban soil aboard the â€œGranma.â€</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79718</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Palacios Ruiz, HÃ©ctor</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2008 July 17</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>One of the founders of the Varela Project, Cuban human rights advocate and one of 75 opposition leaders jailed in March 2003.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79719</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Palmer, Eduardo</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 November 5</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban-born lawyer and film producer whose work includes the documentary Havana: a Portrait of Yesteryear.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79720</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Patterson, Enrique</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 January 26</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Former professor at the University of Havana, Miami journalist, and expert on race relations in Cuba.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79721</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Paz, Luis de la</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 July 26</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban-born writer who came to Miami on the Mariel Boatlift. He has written numerous plays and dramatic works, as well as a column for Diario Las AmÃ©ricas.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79722</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>PedrÃ³n, Luis</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 May 14</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Exiled Cuban guerilla fighter who participated in the 26th of July Movement with Frank PaÃ­s.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79723</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>PerodÃ­n, Sergio</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 May 25</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Survivor of the sinking of the â€œTrece de Marzoâ€ tugboat at Havana harbor in 1994, he lost his wife and an infant son in that tragedy.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79724</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Pichardo, Ernesto</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 November 11</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Co-founder of the Church of LukumÃ­ BabalÃº Aye in Hialeah, Florida and SanterÃ­a priest and advocate. In 1992, his church won the U.S. Supreme Court case against the City of Hialeah over a city ordinance barring the sacrifice of animals during SanterÃ­a religious ceremonies.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79725</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>PiÃ±a, Alicio</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 October 26</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban exile who arrived in Miami alone at the age of 16 and went on to be the first Mariel refugee to receive a law degree from the University of Miami. After serving as chief deputy of Miami-Dade County Courts, he started his own real estate company and is now a partner in Florida Value Partners, a real estate investment firm.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79726</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Portela, Leonor</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 July 12</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban exile widowed in 1961\'s Bay of Pigs invasion, Portela was motivated by a religious experience in the 1980s to sell her Miami home and move to Guatemala where she founded Misioneros del Camino (Missionaries of the Road), an orphanage that currently has its own school and clinic.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79727</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Quadreny, Jorge L.</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 July 2</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban engineer who participated in MRR clandestine cells in Cuba and was a leader of the Cuban exile community in Puerto Rico.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79728</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Quintana, NicolÃ¡s</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2009 October 23</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Renowned Cuban architect and urbanist.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79729</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RamÃ­rez, Rafael \"Felo\"</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2008 December 4</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>The only Cuban sports broadcaster in the Baseball Hall of Fame and a leading force in Cuban sports (especially baseball and boxing) since the 1940s.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79730</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Rasco, JosÃ© Ignacio</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 February 20</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Former leader of the Movimiento DemocrÃ¡tico Cristiano and other Cuban anti-communist organizations.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79731</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Rivera, Agapito</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 January 6</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Known as â€œEl Guajiro Rivera,â€ a living legend among the anti-Castro guerrilla forces of the 1960s. Captured by Castroâ€™s army with so many bullet wounds that he was left to die, he survived and spent many years in prison.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79732</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Rivero, Antonio</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2009 November 5</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Only surviving Rivero brother from the family that made a name for itself in the funerary and florist industry both in Cuba and Miami.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79733</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RoblÃ¡n, Armando</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 June 13</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Miami-based writer, actor and comedian best known for his imitations of Cuban dictator Fidel Castro on television, stage, and film.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79734</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RodrÃ­guez, Ana LÃ¡zara</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 October 18</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Doctor and political prisoner who served 19 years in Cuba.Â  She is the author of Diary of a Survivor (St. Martinâ€™s Press, 1995).</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79735</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RodrÃ­guez, FÃ©lix Ismael</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 June 5</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Former Central Intelligence Agency operative best known for leading the interrogation and execution of Ernesto \"Che\" Guevara in Bolivia in 1967. RodrÃ­guez also participated in the Bay of Pigs invasion, and became president of the Brigade 2506 Veterans Association in 2004.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79736</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RodrÃ­guez de AragÃ³n, Roberto</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 July 14</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Former member of the House of Representatives of Cuba pre-Castro. Because of his close relationship with the Batista family and government, he was among the first Cubans exiled in Miami in 1959 and has served as president of Municipios de Cuba en el Exilio and the Junta PatriÃ³tica Cubana, prominent organizations of their time.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79737</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RomÃ¡n,  AgustÃ­n A. Monsignor</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2009 February 11 ; 2009 March 19</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>First Cuban-born Catholic bishop in the US since the colonial era. Spearheaded the construction of the Ermita de la Caridad shrine.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79738</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>RomanÃ­, Salvador</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 September 12</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Journalist and political leader of the Cuban exile community in Venezuela for over 35 years, with extensive knowledge of that community\'s development and political influence. RomanÃ­ is now a twice-exiled Cuban in Miami.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79739</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Ros, Enrique</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 October 11</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Historian, Bay of Pigs veteran and father of U.S. Representative Ileana Ros-Lehtinen.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79740</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Rosa, Pili de la</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2010 November 10</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Co-founder and director of Sociedad Pro Arte Grateli, Miamiâ€™s oldest Hispanic performing arts company.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79741</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Salvat, Juan Manuel</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2012 August 2</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Cuban activist and dissident who co-founded the anti-Castro organization Directorio Revolucionario Estudiantil (DRE). Salvat actively worked against the Castro government in Cuba, and continued his dissident activities after his exile in 1960. He currently directs the publishing house Ediciones Universales in Miami.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79742</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Santiago, Juan Antonio \"Tony\"</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 January 21</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Renowned labor leader and representative abroad of Partido Social DemÃ³crata Cubano.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79743</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Soto, Osvaldo</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 June 27</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Founder and current president of SALAD (Spanish American League Against Discrimination).</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79744</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>SuÃ¡rez, Diego R.</unittitle>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Graduate of the Civic-Military Institute at Ceiba del Agua, Cuba, who started an agricultural equipment design and manufacturing firm in Havana. Exiled in 1961, he continued in that line of work and today is the largest manufacturer of field equipment for the sugar industry, with accounts in nearly 35 countries. Also prominent in Cuban exile activities, he was one of the founders of the Cuban American National Foundation in 1981 together with the late Jorge Mas Canosa, and he is a leading figure in the Cuban American Liberty Council following a split from CANF after Mas Canosa\'s death.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79745</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>SuÃ¡rez Baster, Rodrigo</unittitle>\n                    <unitdate>2011 November 9</unitdate>\n                  </did>\n                  <scopecontent>\n                    <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                    <p>Member of the House of Representatives of Cuba before the Revolution.</p>\n                  </scopecontent>\n                </c01>\n                <c01 level=\"item\">\n                  <did>\n                    <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79746</unitid>\n                    <unittitle>Tabernilla Palmero, 