odinganalog=\"520$a\" label=\"Abstract\">The RenÃ© Ariza Collection contains drawings, photographs and audiovisual materials of the Cuban writer, director and actor RenÃ© Ariza, active in the late 20th century.</abstract>\n                     \n      </did>\n\n\n      <!--COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA: -->\n               <bioghist altrender=\"Biographical Information\" encodinganalog=\"545\"><head>Biographical Information:</head>\n                              <p>RenÃ© Ariza was a Cuban actor, director and writer born in Havana in 1940. Ariza graduated from the Academia Municipal de Artes DramÃ¡ticas in 1959, eventually receiving the Premio de la UniÃ³n Nacional de Escritores y Artistas de Cuba (UNEAC) in 1967 for his play &quot;La vuelta a la manzana.&quot;</p>\n                                       <p>An opponent of the Castro regime, he was jailed in1974 for his political views until Amnesty International intervened and he was released to the United States in 1979.</p>\n                                       <p>Some of his most well-known plays include &quot;Los tres cerditos y el lobo carnicero,&quot; the aforementioned &quot;La vuelta a la manzana&quot; and &quot;El banquete.&quot; His unpublished work was destroyed during his time in prison, but he continued his creative pursuits until his death in California in 1994.</p>\n                           </bioghist>\n         \n\n            <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n\n                        <controlaccess>\n                     <head>Access Terms</head>\n\n                     <p>This Collection is indexed under the following controlled access subject terms.</p>\n                                 <controlaccess>\n                              <head>Corporate Name:</head>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"local\" role=\"subject\">AgrupaciÃ³n Abdala -- Posters</corpname>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"