e of his works include El Negro en Cuba (1939), Cuba, Tierra Indefensa (1945), and La historia secreta del comunismo cubano y sus purgas (1965). Alberto Arredondo died in Miami on 17 April 1968.</p>\n                           </bioghist>\n         \n\n            <!-- CONTROLLED ACCESS / SUBJECT TERMS -->\n\n                        <controlaccess>\n                     <head>Access Terms</head>\n\n                     <p>This Collection is indexed under the following controlled access subject terms.</p>\n                                 <controlaccess>\n                              <head>Corporate Name:</head>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"local\" role=\"subject\">AgrupaciÃ³n Abdala -- Posters</corpname>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"local\" role=\"subject\">Alpha 66 (Organization)</corpname>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"local\" role=\"subject\">Columbus Memorial Library</corpname>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"local\" role=\"subject\">Sociedad Pro-Arte Musical (Havana, Cuba)</corpname>\n                                       <corpname encodinganalog=\"610\" source=\"local\" role=\"subject\">Universidad de La Habana</corpname>\n                                 </controlaccess>\n                           <controlaccess>\n                              <head>Genre/Form of Material:</head>\n                                       <genreform encodinganalog=\"655\" source=\"local\">Audiocassettes</genreform>\n                                       <genreform encodinganalog=\"655\" source=\"local\">Clippings</genreform>\n                                       <genreform encodinganalog=\"655\" source=\"local\">Documents</genreform>\n                                       <genreform encodinganalog=\"655\" source=\"local\">Letters</genreform>\n                         