nted by panelists at the VI Annual Meeting of ASCE, held at the University of Miami from August 8th-10th, 1996.</p>\n                                 <p>These papers, as well as proceedings from the conference, have been published in a series of <emph render=\"italic\">Cuba in Transition</emph>. Paper topics cover a wide range of subjects, from overviews of the general economic problems of  a transition to a market economy in Cuba to studies of specific economic sectors such as tourism, trade policy, banking, energy, agriculture and the sugar industry.</p>\n                        </scopecontent>\n            \n\n\n         <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n\n         <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n\n                  <!-- END SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n   </archdesc>\n</ead>\n\n','/Applications/MAMP/htdocs/eac/ead/asce_association_for_the_study_of_the_cuban_economy_collection.xml'),(20,'\n<ead audience=\"external\" \n     xmlns=\"urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9\"\n     xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\"\n     xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.loc.gov/ead/ http://www.loc.gov/ead/ead.xsd\">\n   <eadheader langencoding=\"iso639-2b\" audience=\"external\" countryencoding=\"iso3166-1\" dateencoding=\"iso8601\" repositoryencoding=\"iso15511\" scriptencoding=\"iso15924\" relatedencoding=\"MARC21\">\n      <eadid encodinganalog=\"856$u\" mainagencycode=\"US-FQG\" countrycode=\"US\" identifier=\"ArchonInternalCollectionID:308\">01/CHC0509</eadid>\n      <filedesc>\n                  <titlestmt>\n               <titleproper encodinganalog=\"245\">Guide to the AsociaciÃ³n Cubana de Mujeres Universitarias (ACMU) Records</titleproper>\n               <titleproper type=\"filing\">AsociaciÃ³n Cubana de Mujeres Universitarias (ACMU)</titleproper>\n                  </titlestmt>\n         <publicationstmt>\n            <p>&#x00A9; Copyright 2009 University of Miami Cuban Heritage Collection.  All rights r