ten and collected by Cuban writer GastÃ³n Baquero during the last years of his life in Madrid, Spain. The collection includes correspondence, published and unpublished works by Baquero, clippings of newspaper articles by and about Baquero, research notes, photographs, clippings, scrapbooks, awards and memorabilia. Although the collection includes personal papers and documents, the bulk of materials relates to the subjects that occupied Baquero throughout his life, namely Cuban, Spanish and Latin American literature, history and politics.</p>\n                        </scopecontent>\n            \n\n\n         <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n\n         <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n\n                        <!-- BEGIN SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n            <dsc type=\"combined\">\n               <head>Detailed List of Contents</head>\n               <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6279</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Works: Manuscripts and Notes</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>n.d., 1935-1994</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Manuscripts and typescripts of published and unpublished books and articles by GastÃ³n Baquero accompanied by related materials such as correspondence related to their publication. Among these is Baqueroâ€™s unpublished book about AndrÃ©s Bello and related research materials. Also included are articles about Baquero. Subseries C, Conferences and Conference Notes, contains printed materials related to Baqueroâ€™s lectures.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6280</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Books</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\"