ct>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Orchestral music -- Scores and parts</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Performing arts -- Florida -- Miami</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Political parties -- Latin America</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Political posters, Cuban</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Spanish literature -- History and criticism</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Student activities</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Sugar</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Theater -- Cuba -- History -- 20th century</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Theater -- New York (State) -- New York -- History</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Theaters -- United States -- Stage-setting and scenery</subject>\n                                       <subject encodinganalog=\"650\" source=\"local\">Women -- Societies and clubs</subject>\n                                 </controlaccess>\n            </controlaccess>\n            \n\n         <!-- END CONTROLLED ACCESS TERMS -->\n\n            \n            <!-- DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n                              <!-- END DIGITAL ARCHIVAL OBJECTS -->\n                     <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n\n                  <descgrp>\n                     <head>Administrative Information</head>\n                              <acqinfo encodinganalog=\"541\">\n                           <head>Acquisition Information:</head>\n                           <p>Gift of the Batista family, 2005.</p>\n                        </acqinfo>\n                        <processinfo encodinganalog=\"583\">\n                           <head>Processing Information:</head>\n                                    <p>Processed By: Ximena Valdivia, Duvy ArgandoÃ±a, with the assistance of Antonio Mestre, 2007. Edited by Isabel Ezquerra and Esperanza B. de Varona. Encoded by: Ximena Valdivia and Lyn MacCorkle, 2007.</p>\n                              </processinfo>\n                              <userestrict encodinganalog=\"540\">\n                           <head>Conditions Governing Use:</head>\n                                          <p><emph render=\"bold\">Guidelines for Accessing the Fulgencio Batista Zaldivar Collection</emph></p>\n                                          <p>The finding aid for this collection is available online at <extref linktype=\"simple\" audience=\"external\" show=\"embed\" actuate=\"onrequest\" href=\"http://proust.library.miami.edu/findingaids/?p=collections/findingaid&amp;id=52\">http://proust.library.miami.edu/findingaids/?p=collections/findingaid&amp;id=52</extref>.</p>\n                                          <p>Researchers visiting the Cuban Heritage Collection can request to see any of the boxes in the Batista collection <emph render=\"bold\"><emph render=\"underline\">except</emph></emph> boxes 60 and 97 (restricted).</p>\n                                          <p>Researchers may <emph render=\"bold\"><emph render=\"underline\">not</emph></emph> request photocopies of anything in Series I (boxes 1 to 6).</p>\n                                          <p>Researchers may obtain photocopies of anything in boxes 7 through 148 <emph render=\"bold\"><emph render=\"underline\">except</emph></emph> boxes 60 and 97 (restricted).</p>\n                                          <p>Researchers may <emph render=\"bold\"><emph render=\"underline\">not</emph></emph> use a personal digital camera to photograph any part of the Batista collection.</p>\n                                          <p>All permissions to quote or publish materials from the Batista collection must be approved in writing by the FBZ Archivos Foundation.Â  Researchers interested in digital reproductions of materials from this collection may complete Licensing Application form available at the Reading Room desk.Â  CHC staff will help researchers contact the FBZ Archivos Foundation to request permission to reproduce, quote, and publish materials.</p>\n                                          <p>Materials in the Fulgencio Batista Zaldivar Collection have been donated by the FBZ Archivos Foundation.Â  Materials related to Fulgencio Batista Zaldivar and found in other collections held by the Cuban Heritage Collection are not subject to the guidelines here outlined.</p>\n                                          <p>Requests to publish or display materials from this collection require written permission from the rights owner. Please, contact chc@miami.edu for more information.</p>\n                              </userestrict>\n                     <accessrestrict encodinganalog=\"506\">\n                        <head>Conditions Governing Access:</head>\n                                          <p>Access to the Fulgencio Batista ZaldÃ­var Collection is unrestricted.</p>\n                                          <p>Copyright to the collection is retained by the FBZ Foundation. The Following must be approved in writing by the FBZ Foundation: 1) photocopy requests for items found in Series I: Core Selections from Correspondence and Correspondent Files and Photographs; 2) all requests for digital reproductions; and 3) all requests to use materials from this collection for publication, broadcast, or any other uses which can be interpreted as beyond fair use as defined by copyright laws.</p>\n                           </accessrestrict>\n                              <prefercite encodinganalog=\"524\">\n                     <head>Preferred Citation:</head>\n                     <p>Fulgencio Batista ZaldÃ­var Collection, Cuban Heritage Collection, University of Miami Libraries.</p>\n                     </prefercite>\n                     </descgrp>\n\n                           <arrangement encodinganalog=\"351\">\n                  <head>Arrangement of Materials:</head>\n                                 <p>The Fulgencio Batista ZaldÃ­var Collection is organized into seven series by content type.</p>\n                        </arrangement>\n            <scopecontent>\n               <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                                 <p>The bulk of the collection consists of correspondence with Cuban government and military officials, some prior to 1959, and with prominent political and literary figures.</p>\n                                 <p>The collection also includes manuscripts of an unpublished autobiography and other books, as well as published books and pamphlets written by Batista. Other materials include periodicals and books collected by Batista, some inscribed by the authors, as well as photographs of both personal and official nature, memorabilia, and notes and statistics on social and economic conditions in Cuba during the Batista era.</p>\n                        </scopecontent>\n            \n\n\n         <!-- END ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->\n\n         <!-- END COLLECTION LEVEL METADATA -->\n\n                        <!-- BEGIN SUBORDINATE COMPONENTS -->\n            <dsc type=\"combined\">\n               <head>Detailed List of Contents</head>\n               <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id6476</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Core Selections from Correspondence and Correspondent Files and Photographs</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Items in this series were selected for digitization by the donor as the most important in the collection. They include letters and other correspondence including manuscripts, clippings, programs and other items sent and received by Fulgencio Batista and selected because of the prominence of the correspondents, and a selection of photographs including photos of Fulgencio Batista, his family and their personal surroundings, official portraits and groups, and other photographs of Batista government associates, public works and events of that era.	Subseries A-D is arranged alphabetically by name of correspondent; arranged as follows under each name: correspondence by and to Batista, related clippings, documents, publications and works by others; subseries E is arranged by association/institution with correspondentsâ€™ names in alphabetical order within each category. Photographs in sub-series F-H are arranged chronologically by decade; F and G are further subdivided as portraits, group photographs, official events and visits, etc.; sub-series I is grouped by subject with folders in alphabetical order by name; folders sub-subseries 2, Public Works, are arranged in broad categories by type of work (e.g. bridges, roads,).	Note: Items in this series were selected by the donor as the most important.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63803</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents A-D</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63804</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents E-L</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63805</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents M-Q</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63806</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents R-Z</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63807</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Other Correspondents</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63808</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Associations and Institutions</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63809</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Government Officials</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63810</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Journalists and Writers</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63811</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Military Officials</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63812</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Photographs - Batista ZaldÃ­var, Fulgencio</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63813</unitid>\n               <unittitle>FernÃ¡ndez de Batista, Marta de</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63814</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Photographs - The Batista Family</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63815</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Other Photographs</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63816</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Associations and Institutions</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63817</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Batista Government Public Works</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63818</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Other Topics</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   \n</c02>\n   \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63791</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondence and Correspondent Files</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Letters and other correspondence including manuscripts, clippings, programs and other items sent and received by Fulgencio Batista. Sub-series A through D contain extensive correspondence and related documents mainly from important figures. Sub-series E contains correspondence grouped by affiliation.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63792</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents A-D</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63793</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents E-L</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63794</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents M-Q</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63795</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Correspondents R-Z</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63797</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Other Correspondents</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63798</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Associations and Institutions</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63799</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Government Officials</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63801</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Journalists and Writers</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   <c03 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63802</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Military Officials</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c03>\n   \n</c02>\n   \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63819</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Works: Manuscripts and Notes</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Manuscripts of works by Fulgencio Batista, related research notes and other materials, including: synopsis or outline; research material and notes; bibliographies; drafts; translations and foreign editions; galley proofs; revisions; related materials: advertisements, publicity, press releases and reviews. The series also inludes manuscripts by others. Subseries A and B contain manuscripts by Batista of published and unpublished works each with related materials; C has research notes of unidentified materials; D has works by others. Works by Fulgencio Batista in alphabetical order by title; works by others in alphabetical order by title within authorâ€™s name.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63820</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Published by FBZ</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63821</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Unpublished by FBZ</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63822</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Unidentified</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63823</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Works by others</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63824</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Personal Files</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Sub-series A and B: Transcripts and copies of interviews and speeches of Fulgencio Batista and related materials; C: clippings about Fulgencio Batista and clippings related to his travels; D: memoranda by Batista on various topics; E: notes collected by Batista about economic and social conditions in Cuba during his government; F: transcripts and copies of awards received by Batista; G: magazines with cover articles of Batista and his government; H: funeral documents of Fulgencio Batista, his brother Francisco (PanchÃ­n) and his son Carlos Manuel.	Sub-series A, B, D and G are in chronological order except for the March 10 and September 4 anniversary speeches; C in alphabetical order by topic within chronological order; E in creator-assigned order; F in collector-assigned categories: â€œCondecoraciones nacionales y extranjerasâ€ (national and international decorations of honor, â€œDiplomasâ€ (recognitions) and â€œPergaminosâ€ (scrolls); G by date and publication title; F arranged as follows under each decedent: correspondence related to Carlos Manuel and â€œPanchÃ­nâ€™sâ€ funerals by collector-assigned numbers; correspondence related to Fulgencio Batistaâ€™s funeral in alphabetical order by correspondentâ€™s name followed by clippings arranged by country of origin and publication title.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63825</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Speeches</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63826</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Interviews</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63827</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Clippings</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63828</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Memoranda</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63829</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Notes</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63830</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Awards</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63831</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Magazine Covers</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63832</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Funerals</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63833</unitid>\n               <unittitle>BAR (â€œBurÃ³ de aclaraciones y respuestasâ€)</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Documents relating to this informal organization created to provide information about Batistaâ€™s government, in most cases in reply to published articles. Items are arranged in chronological order.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"series\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63834</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Other Documents</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Documents collected by Batista under the title â€œDocumentos variosâ€ not related to his publications. Sub-series A contains depositions given to the US Congress by former US Ambassadors to Cuba; B includes documents and correspondence related to the so-called â€œPlan Torrienteâ€ proposed by JosÃ© ElÃ­as de la Torriente to liberate Cuba; C has transcripts and notes of the 1956 and 1967 Meetings of the American Chiefs of State; D is comprised by statistics mainly about agriculture and other aspects of the Cuban economy; E contains press releases from various agencies primarily related to Cuban politics; F contains memorabilia about his political campaigns; G groups other memorabilia; H contains other documents mainly related to the Batista government administrative aspects and public works.	Subseries A is in alphabetical order by name of deponent; B, C, D, F and G in chronological order; E by topic (e.g. Batista government, Cuban Refugees, etc.); H by institution or association (e.g. Organization of American States, â€œONCEP, OrganizaciÃ³n Nacional de Comedores Escolares Popularesâ€).</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63835</unitid>\n               <unittitle>â€œAudiencias y testimoniosâ€</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63836</unitid>\n               <unittitle>â€œPlan Torrienteâ€</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63837</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Meetings of the American Chiefs of State</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63838</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Statistics</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63839</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Press Releases</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id63840</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Memorabilia, Political Campaigns</unittitle>\n               </did>\n         \n</c02>\n   <c02 level=\"subseries\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" 