                  <unitdate>2010 July 17</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Renowned physician.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79662</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Benes, Bernardo</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2009 July 23</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Leader of the Cuban Jewish community who played a pivotal role in the â€œdiÃ¡logoâ€ with the Castro government in the late 1970sÂ during Â Jimmy Carter&#039;s presidency.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79663</unitid>\n               <unittitle>BengurÃ­a, Carmina</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2011 June 29</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Cuban poet and last surviving â€œrecitadoraâ€ of the 1940s and 1950s, who attained fame in 1959, at the triumph of the Revolution, for her rendering of the Marcha Triunfal del EjÃ©rcito Rebelde, only to became a Cuban exile soon after.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79664</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Bichachi, Israel</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2011 October 12</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Havana-born, Sephardic Jewish activist who joined a group of Cuban Jews to fight for Israel&#039;s independence. Upon returning to Cuba, he left as an exile in 1961, living in Israel and New York before settling in Miami and opening the