   <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79668</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Cao M.D., AndrÃ©s</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2010 December 16</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Cuban physician and former member of the Movimiento de RecuperaciÃ³n Revolucionaria (MRR), a Cuban counterrevolutionary group. Dr. Cao was arrested and condemned to 20 years in prison as a political prisoner.Â  He is the author of La verdadera RepÃºblica de Cuba (Ediciones Universal, 2008).</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79669</unitid>\n               <unittitle>CÃ¡rdenas, Isidro</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2012 May 29</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Interviewed with Neida Revuelta, husband and wife Cuban folksingers best known for their Spanish-language radio program with La Poderosa station in Miami.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79670</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Castillo, Amelia del</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2012 May 23</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Well-known poet, essayist, and narrator.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79671</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Castillo, Siro  del</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2011 October 3</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>A human rights advocate and community leader on immigrant issues, del Castillo worked as an architectural designer for Cuba&#039;s National Institute of Tourism and left the island in 1972. During the Mariel boatlift, del Castillo assumed a variety of responsibilities with the county and federal government&#039;s efforts to manage the crisis and provide services for refugees. Since then, he has continued to work on behalf of Cuban and other immigrants in the U.S. as well as in defense of human rights in the Caribbean. During the Cuban Rafter Crisis of 1994, he was named Assistant to the Ombudsman for the General at GuantÃ¡namo Naval Base. He is active on the boards of several civic organizations and is recognized for his community leadership.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79672</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Chirino, Willy</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2012 July 16</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Renowned Cuban-American salsa singer and music producer. Chirino has recorded over 20 albums since 1974, winning a Grammy in 2006 for Best Salsa/Merengue Album.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79673</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Chorens, Olga</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2008 June 4</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Cuban singer and half of the entertainment duo â€œOlga y Tony.â€ Pioneer of TV in Cuba and Puerto Rico and of Spanish TV in the U.S.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79674</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Clark, Juan M.</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2011 June 21</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Well-known sociologist, and professor emeritus at Miami Dade College. A Bay of Pigs veteran and former political prisoner, Dr. Clark is the author, among other works, of Cuba, mito y realidad (Saeta Ediciones, 1992).</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79675</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Conte AgÃ¼ero, Luis</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2008 October 30; 2008 November 21</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Journalist and political figure in pre-Castro Cubaâ€™s Ortodoxo party. School friend of Fidel Castro and his first biographer.Â  Anti-Castro exile leader.Â </p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79676</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Cros Sandoval, Mercedes</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2008 May 21</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Anthropologist and scholar of Afro-Cuban religion.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79677</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Cruz Varela, MarÃ­a Elena</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2012 September 5</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Cuban poet, activist, and political prisoner. Cruz Varela led a group of anti-Castro dissidents called Critico Alternativo, which published a manifesto of grievances and reforms against the government in 1991. She was awarded the Liberal Institute Prize for Freedom in 1992.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79678</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Cutillas, Manuel J.</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2011 December 22</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Former Chairman of the Board and CEO of BacardÃ­ Ltd.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79679</unitid>\n               <unittitle>DÃ­az, GuarionÃ©</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2010 August 10</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Pedro Pan child and founder and president of the Cuban American National Council.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79680</unitid>\n               <unittitle>DÃ­az, Sonia</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2012 June 11</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Interviewed with Martha del Pino, two Miami-area ballet instructors who founded the Coral Gables-based Academia Cubana de Ballet.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79681</unitid>\n               <unittitle>DÃ­az-Balart, Lincoln</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2011 November 7</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Retired Republican U.S. Congressman from Florida who served in the Florida State House of Representatives from 1987 to 1989, the Florida Senate from 1989 to 1992, and the U.S. House of Representatives from 1993 to 2011.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79682</unitid>\n               <unittitle>DÃ­az Espinosa, Maribel</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2012 June 26</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Daughter of renowned Cuban pianist and music instructor Conchita Espinosa. Conchita founded music academies in Cuba and the United States, receiving numerous awards as a distinguished educator. Maribel currently runs her late mother&#039;s school, Conchita Espinosa Academy.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79683</unitid>\n               <unittitle>DÃºran, Alfredo</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2010 November 5</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <head>Scope and Contents</head>\n                  <p>Bay of Pigs veteran who chaired the Florida Democratic Party from 1976 to 1980.Â  Appointed by Florida governor Reubin Askew in 1973, he was the first Hispanic to serve on the Miami-Dade County School Board. A former president of the Veteranâ€™s Association of Brigade 2506, DurÃ¡n was asked to step down for his support of a dialogue with the Cuban government to bring about a transition in Cuba.Â  He founded the Cuban Committee for Democracy in 1993.</p>\n                     </scopecontent>\n            \n</c01>\n   <c01 level=\"item\">\n   <did>\n      <unitid label=\"ArchonID\" audience=\"internal\">id79684</unitid>\n               <unittitle>Fajardo, Josefina</unittitle>\n                  <unitdate>2010 October 20</unitdate>\n               </did>\n         <scopecontent>\n      <h